1
00:01:13,200 --> 00:01:18,000
<i>[Meet Yourself]</i>

2
00:01:19,370 --> 00:01:23,450
<i>[Episode 32]</i>

3
00:01:45,710 --> 00:01:49,323
<i>[My Father]</i>

4
00:01:57,500 --> 00:02:01,600
Jiahui, you know me.

5
00:02:01,600 --> 00:02:04,600
Should I make this call or not?

6
00:02:07,500 --> 00:02:09,600
Who's this?

7
00:02:12,600 --> 00:02:15,400
Hello?

8
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:19,600
Dessert store?

9
00:02:20,600 --> 00:02:22,200
Jin...

10
00:02:25,100 --> 00:02:27,600
It's just a misunderstanding.

11
00:02:27,600 --> 00:02:28,800
A misunderstanding.

12
00:02:28,800 --> 00:02:32,000
Don't worry. I've put it behind me.

13
00:02:37,900 --> 00:02:39,100
Please, Miss.

14
00:02:39,100 --> 00:02:41,000
I can't run my business.

15
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:43,800
I already told you that I'd apologize.

16
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:45,700
Why should you apologize?

17
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:49,300
The ones who messed up should apologize.

18
00:02:49,300 --> 00:02:52,400
Call those guys back, the one called Niqiu and the rest.

19
00:02:52,400 --> 00:02:54,300
They aren't locals.

20
00:02:54,300 --> 00:02:56,200
They only came over to hang out with me.

21
00:02:56,200 --> 00:02:57,800
I don't care.

22
00:02:57,800 --> 00:03:01,200
I already called Hu Youyu.

23
00:03:01,200 --> 00:03:02,400
He's already put it behind him.

24
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:04,300
Why are you being so nosy?

25
00:03:04,300 --> 00:03:07,800
Listen. We're in the same situation.

26
00:03:07,800 --> 00:03:09,600
You're protecting your buddies.

27
00:03:09,600 --> 00:03:12,300
I have to protect mine, too.

28
00:03:12,300 --> 00:03:14,600
If you loiter here, I can only call the police.

29
00:03:14,600 --> 00:03:16,200
Go ahead.

30
00:03:18,400 --> 00:03:19,600
Please, Miss!

31
00:03:19,600 --> 00:03:22,300
I'm begging you!

32
00:03:22,300 --> 00:03:23,600
I really...

33
00:03:24,700 --> 00:03:26,200
Sister!

34
00:03:26,200 --> 00:03:28,000
What are you doing?

35
00:03:30,600 --> 00:03:34,000
Are you... Mr. Hu Youyu?

36
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:35,800
J-Just call me Xiao Hu.

37
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:37,600
You're Jin, right?

38
00:03:37,600 --> 00:03:39,700
Yes! I'm Jin.

39
00:03:39,700 --> 00:03:42,000
Mr. Hu!

40
00:03:43,400 --> 00:03:44,800
Here's the thing.

41
00:03:44,800 --> 00:03:49,800
I was planning to apologize to you in person soon,

42
00:03:49,800 --> 00:03:54,600
but this lady insists on asking my buddies to do it.

43
00:03:54,600 --> 00:03:56,000
They aren't locals.

44
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:57,800
They only came over to hang out with me.

45
00:03:57,800 --> 00:03:59,500
Flight tickets aren't cheap either.

46
00:03:59,500 --> 00:04:02,400
It costs a few thousand for all three of them.

47
00:04:02,400 --> 00:04:03,900
They're regular employees without much money.

48
00:04:03,900 --> 00:04:07,200
If you're fine with a phone call apology, I'll get them to call you.

49
00:04:07,200 --> 00:04:09,200
It's really no big deal. You don't have to do that.

50
00:04:09,200 --> 00:04:11,300
I don't mind. It's just a misunderstanding.

51
00:04:11,300 --> 00:04:12,700
Yes, a misunderstanding.

52
00:04:12,700 --> 00:04:13,800
Just a misunderstanding.

53
00:04:13,800 --> 00:04:15,500
Mr. Hu, here's the thing.

54
00:04:15,500 --> 00:04:18,200
Shes been sitting here for days.

55
00:04:18,200 --> 00:04:20,300
For days?

56
00:04:20,300 --> 00:04:24,000
Now, everyone knows about this.

57
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:25,200
It's too embarrassing!

58
00:04:25,200 --> 00:04:28,800
A small business like mine can't survive large tides.

59
00:04:29,500 --> 00:04:33,400
Brother, I didn't know about this either. I'm really sorry.

60
00:04:33,400 --> 00:04:36,400
No, I should be the one apologizing. I'm sorry.

61
00:04:36,400 --> 00:04:38,700
- No. I'm sorry.
- Okay, fine.

62
00:04:42,400 --> 00:04:46,400
Sister, I thought you went out to have fun.

63
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:49,600
I'm really not bothered by this matter.

64
00:04:49,600 --> 00:04:51,800
It's embarrassing to be stared at by a crowd.

65
00:04:51,800 --> 00:04:53,400
It's fine.

66
00:04:53,400 --> 00:04:55,300
He doesn't care anyway.

67
00:04:57,200 --> 00:04:59,600
Sister, how about I treat you to a meal at Galsang Flower Restaurant?

68
00:04:59,600 --> 00:05:01,000
Let's have lunch, okay?

69
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:02,200
Come on! Time for lunch!

70
00:05:02,200 --> 00:05:03,800
Let's go!

71
00:05:05,600 --> 00:05:07,600
I'll give you two days.

72
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:09,100
No, it's fine.

73
00:05:09,100 --> 00:05:10,600
Don't worry. We won't come back.

74
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:12,000
Have a booming business!

75
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:13,500
Let's go.

76
00:05:13,500 --> 00:05:15,100
Watch your step.

77
00:05:15,100 --> 00:05:16,600
Two days!

78
00:05:16,600 --> 00:05:18,400
Let's go!

79
00:05:21,800 --> 00:05:23,500
Here you go.

80
00:05:24,400 --> 00:05:26,800
Okay, let's go. Sit in the back.

81
00:05:48,600 --> 00:05:50,800
Why are you staring at me?

82
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:52,400
Sister, try this.

83
00:05:52,400 --> 00:05:54,380
This is good. It's is their specialty.

84
00:05:54,380 --> 00:05:56,220
Have a taste.

85
00:06:00,800 --> 00:06:02,900
Speak your mind.

86
00:06:05,300 --> 00:06:10,900
Shall we talk this through?

87
00:06:10,900 --> 00:06:13,400
Let's put this behind us.

88
00:06:13,400 --> 00:06:19,600
Actually, I feel uneasy if you insist on doing this.

89
00:06:19,600 --> 00:06:21,200
They've already left.

90
00:06:21,200 --> 00:06:24,400
It's preposterous to call them back.

91
00:06:24,400 --> 00:06:26,300
As the saying goes,

92
00:06:26,300 --> 00:06:30,300
"Forgiving others is to forgive yourself."

93
00:06:32,400 --> 00:06:35,300
You must think that I'm putting my finger in your pie.

94
00:06:35,300 --> 00:06:36,400
Nope.

95
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:37,800
Not at all.

96
00:06:37,800 --> 00:06:39,400
I never felt that way.

97
00:06:39,400 --> 00:06:41,300
I promise.

98
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:49,000
I just feel a little puzzled.

99
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:52,000
It's a little... excessive.

100
00:06:54,200 --> 00:06:59,500
That's because this matter isn't a problem, to begin with. Right?

101
00:07:00,500 --> 00:07:04,400
Besides, we barely got to know each other.

102
00:07:04,400 --> 00:07:07,000
We're just friends living in the same courtyard.

103
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:09,200
You're too nice to me.

104
00:07:09,200 --> 00:07:15,400
I... I don't deserve this.

105
00:07:19,300 --> 00:07:20,800
Yes, that's all.

106
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:25,000
I understand.

107
00:07:26,400 --> 00:07:28,600
But don't you want to give it a shot?

108
00:07:36,500 --> 00:07:38,900
G-Give what a shot?

109
00:07:39,900 --> 00:07:42,400
Earning some respect from others.

110
00:07:47,200 --> 00:07:50,100
R-Respect?

111
00:07:50,100 --> 00:07:51,800
Sister, listen up.

112
00:07:51,800 --> 00:07:53,100
Ever since I started my music career,

113
00:07:53,100 --> 00:07:56,400
I've put down all my pride.

114
00:07:56,400 --> 00:08:00,400
I only came this far thanks to my audacity and shamelessness.

115
00:08:00,400 --> 00:08:03,500
If I can't accept being hustled or mocked a little,

116
00:08:03,500 --> 00:08:05,900
I'd be suffering from depression by now.

117
00:08:08,500 --> 00:08:14,400
Moreover, I owe all of these to my dad.

118
00:08:14,400 --> 00:08:17,100
When I was in a band, my dad objected.

119
00:08:17,100 --> 00:08:18,700
He refused to let me do what I wanted.

120
00:08:18,700 --> 00:08:20,800
When I finally clinched a gig,

121
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:23,700
my old man took a taxi over and ruined the show.

122
00:08:23,700 --> 00:08:29,600
He smashed my guitar and my bandmate's drums.

123
00:08:29,600 --> 00:08:31,000
He has a terrible temper.

124
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:33,600
He's already in this state,

125
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:39,200
but he'd smash cups if he heard my mom on the phone with me.

126
00:08:46,800 --> 00:08:50,800
Xiao Yu, you've been through a lot,

127
00:08:50,800 --> 00:08:53,200
but I think you're talented.

128
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:57,400
Remember when you sang "Wind" at the live house in Beijing?

129
00:08:57,400 --> 00:09:00,500
I thought it was a marvelous song when I heard it.

130
00:09:00,500 --> 00:09:02,300
It left a deep impression in my mind instantly.

131
00:09:03,700 --> 00:09:05,800
You're truly brilliant,

132
00:09:05,800 --> 00:09:10,800
but not every gifted person is acknowledged in this world.

133
00:09:17,100 --> 00:09:18,700
You need to make a living.

134
00:09:18,700 --> 00:09:20,600
You sing at the bar,

135
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:24,000
but these aren't reasons to be trampled over by others.

136
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:29,300
Got it?

137
00:09:41,800 --> 00:09:43,500
Come on, Uncle.

138
00:09:43,500 --> 00:09:44,800
Of course.

139
00:09:44,800 --> 00:09:46,100
All right.

140
00:09:50,300 --> 00:09:52,000
The dishes are ready.

141
00:09:53,600 --> 00:09:55,800
Here. Put it in front of Uncle Deqing.

142
00:09:55,800 --> 00:09:57,000
Okay, you must have been waiting for a long time.

143
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:59,000
Come on.

144
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:02,600
- Okay.
- I can reach it.

145
00:10:02,600 --> 00:10:07,700
A'Yao, I saw you showing the bookstore owner around our village.

146
00:10:07,700 --> 00:10:09,000
How are things going?

147
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:10,900
The deal hasn't been sealed yet.

148
00:10:12,800 --> 00:10:15,000
When is Honghong returning?

149
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:16,800
She just left.

150
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:17,800
Tickets are expensive.

151
00:10:17,800 --> 00:10:20,000
Why would she come back so often?

152
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:21,200
Enjoy your food.

153
00:10:21,200 --> 00:10:22,300
Call me if you need anything.

154
00:10:22,300 --> 00:10:24,400
Okay, you can get on with your work.

155
00:10:32,300 --> 00:10:34,000
You have to understand this.

156
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:37,600
Grandpa is old and has a bad temper.

157
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:40,500
It's good if someone wants to rent the old house.

158
00:10:40,500 --> 00:10:41,700
I have no objections.

159
00:10:41,700 --> 00:10:45,300
It's a contribution to our village's income anyway.

160
00:10:45,300 --> 00:10:47,200
You're absolutely right.

161
00:10:49,400 --> 00:10:53,500
A'Yao, I know it's hard to boost the village's tourism.

162
00:10:53,500 --> 00:10:56,800
I'm childhood friends with your dad.

163
00:10:56,800 --> 00:10:58,300
I really want to help you,

164
00:10:58,300 --> 00:11:01,400
but I don't know how I can help.

165
00:11:01,400 --> 00:11:05,300
You devoted so much to this bookstore.

166
00:11:05,300 --> 00:11:08,800
It'll be great for you if the bookstore opens here.

167
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:11,700
Uncle, you're right,

168
00:11:11,700 --> 00:11:14,100
but the house belongs to Grandpa Yang.

169
00:11:14,100 --> 00:11:15,500
I need his approval.

170
00:11:15,500 --> 00:11:18,000
Persuade him if you have a chance.

171
00:11:19,300 --> 00:11:22,200
Let's seal the deal with the bookstore first.

172
00:11:22,200 --> 00:11:25,200
Leave the rest to me.

173
00:11:25,200 --> 00:11:27,900
Uncle, get his approval first.

174
00:11:27,900 --> 00:11:29,400
The house belongs to him.

175
00:11:29,400 --> 00:11:31,800
We have to respect his decision.

176
00:11:31,800 --> 00:11:34,000
Don't worry. I'll make it work.

177
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:35,600
Come on.

178
00:11:42,800 --> 00:11:45,600
This is a good deal for both of us.

179
00:11:45,600 --> 00:11:46,600
We're allies.

180
00:11:46,600 --> 00:11:48,300
I believe in you.

181
00:11:48,300 --> 00:11:50,800
Xiao Huang needs results for her career,

182
00:11:50,800 --> 00:11:53,600
and we want profits.

183
00:11:54,800 --> 00:11:59,700
Uncle, just voice your requests honestly.

184
00:11:59,700 --> 00:12:02,200
I'll try to get them fulfilled for you.

185
00:12:04,700 --> 00:12:08,200
Since we're the only ones here, I'll be frank.

186
00:12:09,200 --> 00:12:12,700
I'm not asking for much rent.

187
00:12:12,700 --> 00:12:16,800
The rate can be similar to the house of Xiao Gang's aunt.

188
00:12:16,800 --> 00:12:18,800
Xiao Gang's aunt?

189
00:12:18,800 --> 00:12:20,200
Where is it?

190
00:12:34,440 --> 00:12:37,230
Here, have some tea.

191
00:12:37,230 --> 00:12:39,439
- Thank you.
- Thanks.

192
00:12:43,510 --> 00:12:45,650
This tea is good.

193
00:12:45,650 --> 00:12:47,039
It's Mr. Ma's tea.

194
00:12:47,039 --> 00:12:51,690
Mr. Ma said that drinking gongfu tea is also a good way to cultivate your mind.

195
00:12:53,680 --> 00:12:58,469
So, Uncle Deqing can persuade Grandpa Yang to rent out the house,

196
00:12:58,469 --> 00:13:01,159
but he's asking for quite a pricey rent.

197
00:13:01,159 --> 00:13:04,320
It's more than that. It's exorbitant.

198
00:13:04,320 --> 00:13:07,920
If he only wanted to raise it slightly, we can negotiate for him.

199
00:13:07,920 --> 00:13:10,832
But he wants the rent of a tourist hot spot.

200
00:13:10,832 --> 00:13:13,549
He even said that money definitely isn't a problem for the boss.

201
00:13:13,549 --> 00:13:15,059
That's not the problem!

202
00:13:15,060 --> 00:13:18,550
We can't negotiate with such greedy demands.

203
00:13:18,550 --> 00:13:22,470
I think you shouldn't tell the bookstore team first.

204
00:13:22,470 --> 00:13:27,560
If it were me, I'd think that the people here were rude.

205
00:13:27,560 --> 00:13:29,870
They're trying to make a buck off me immediately.

206
00:13:29,870 --> 00:13:31,620
That's my worry as well.

207
00:13:31,620 --> 00:13:34,420
We can only settle this by ourselves.

208
00:13:34,420 --> 00:13:37,860
Can we ask for a plot of land from the village committee?

209
00:13:38,440 --> 00:13:39,840
The land here is limited.

210
00:13:39,840 --> 00:13:42,109
Agricultural land can't be used either.

211
00:13:42,109 --> 00:13:44,589
Besides, the boss prefers that old estate.

212
00:13:44,589 --> 00:13:46,910
What a headache.

213
00:13:46,910 --> 00:13:50,039
Don't worry. I'll discuss this with him tomorrow.

214
00:13:58,840 --> 00:14:01,379
We can negotiate the payment method.

215
00:14:01,380 --> 00:14:02,509
A payment of five-years each time.

216
00:14:02,509 --> 00:14:05,690
We'll let Xiao Huang discuss progressive increases.

217
00:14:05,690 --> 00:14:10,610
However, without existing profits, it's unreasonable to ask for pricey rent.

218
00:14:10,610 --> 00:14:14,450
A'Yao, you can't speak for capitalists.

219
00:14:14,450 --> 00:14:17,230
You have to side with me. We're in the same boat.

220
00:14:17,230 --> 00:14:19,460
Yes, Uncle Deqing.

221
00:14:19,460 --> 00:14:21,600
But the rent...

222
00:14:21,600 --> 00:14:23,850
If you don't want to offend them, I can talk to them.

223
00:14:23,850 --> 00:14:25,530
I can be audacious.

224
00:14:26,280 --> 00:14:28,660
It's not like that.

225
00:14:28,660 --> 00:14:30,630
This meat is good. Get me another serving.

226
00:14:37,560 --> 00:14:40,560
Shall we get Engineer Zhang to view a different spot?

227
00:14:41,710 --> 00:14:44,509
Didn't they find it problematic that the shuttle bus couldn't get in?

228
00:14:44,509 --> 00:14:48,160
I convinced them that the place has a nice and quiet ambiance.

229
00:14:48,160 --> 00:14:50,830
Walking and cycling would also be a draw for tourists.

230
00:14:50,830 --> 00:14:52,240
Yes.

231
00:14:52,240 --> 00:14:53,869
I've said everything I could.

232
00:14:53,869 --> 00:14:57,000
I have no other solutions in mind.

233
00:14:58,840 --> 00:15:01,850
Let me talk to him tomorrow.

234
00:15:07,800 --> 00:15:09,749
I'm in charge of this matter.

235
00:15:09,749 --> 00:15:13,090
I'll try my best to raise the rent reasonably.

236
00:15:13,090 --> 00:15:14,559
This is very reasonable.

237
00:15:14,559 --> 00:15:17,440
It's my house, so I should be able to decide on the rent.

238
00:15:17,440 --> 00:15:19,590
Why is this unreasonable?

239
00:15:20,200 --> 00:15:23,800
Yes, you're right.

240
00:15:23,800 --> 00:15:26,409
Xiao Huang, I think you're a good village officer.

241
00:15:26,409 --> 00:15:27,990
You've done so much for the people.

242
00:15:27,990 --> 00:15:30,050
You're on the same side as us.

243
00:15:30,050 --> 00:15:33,159
I also think you're capable of anything you set your eyes on.

244
00:15:33,159 --> 00:15:34,799
That's because you're a university graduate.

245
00:15:34,799 --> 00:15:38,790
You're cultured, capable, educated, kind, and upright.

246
00:15:38,790 --> 00:15:42,559
Our humble village is honored by your presence.

247
00:15:42,559 --> 00:15:46,260
It's like the skies have been painted in gold, shimmering bright.

248
00:15:46,260 --> 00:15:49,049
- I'll wait for your good news.
- Okay.

249
00:15:50,260 --> 00:15:52,470
Are these for my dad?

250
00:15:53,210 --> 00:15:56,190
Yes. They are. I almost forgot about them.

251
00:15:56,190 --> 00:15:58,039
How thoughtful.

252
00:15:58,039 --> 00:15:59,729
Thank you. I'll wait for your good news.

253
00:15:59,729 --> 00:16:01,280
Okay.

254
00:16:20,780 --> 00:16:22,260
What are you doing?

255
00:16:22,260 --> 00:16:26,630
I'm stripping away all the flattery Uncle Deqing stacked on me.

256
00:16:27,210 --> 00:16:28,690
Listen up.

257
00:16:28,690 --> 00:16:32,750
Uncle Deqing is like a piece of hob meat.

258
00:16:33,510 --> 00:16:34,920
What? What's hob meat?

259
00:16:34,920 --> 00:16:38,470
You see, hob meat is hard to cut, hard to cook, and hard to chew.

260
00:16:38,470 --> 00:16:42,900
Such meat is full of tendons, and the skin is thick.

261
00:16:42,900 --> 00:16:45,709
All he has are persistent unreasonable demands and no ears.

262
00:16:45,709 --> 00:16:47,730
You're at a loss when facing him.

263
00:16:48,680 --> 00:16:50,059
Hob meat!

264
00:16:50,060 --> 00:16:52,040
That's just like him!

265
00:16:52,040 --> 00:16:55,109
There was another incident with the town's development.

266
00:16:55,109 --> 00:16:57,470
After the contract was signed and the rent was confirmed,

267
00:16:57,470 --> 00:17:00,429
the landlord raised a ruckus with some men for a higher rent.

268
00:17:00,429 --> 00:17:01,999
